data.text: @laRosalind @MSCasting Ha! Tru...
@WBEngMG @MSCasting ah, sweet sweet overtime...

@laRosalind @MSCasting Hi, Rosalind 😷 wanted to also let you know I didn’t see a single protestor today when navigating Dodger Stadium. However, on my way out (near the public recreational area) I saw an unbelievable 2 dz plus police SUV’s in a staging area all mulling about. I guess they’re ready...

@laRosalind @WBEngMG I wish I did! I didn’t know much about LA’s system until a friend contacted me on Thursday. He educated me then pressured me to get an appointment that day at Dodger Stadium. Since then I’ve tried to tell as many people what I’ve learned. Things should get much easier soon w/ j&j

@laRosalind @MSCasting I’ll let you know - I’m almost first thing in the morning. My ‘67 Volvo Amazon was built to navigate up/over rough Swedish terrain, so, a few ‘bumps’ in the road shouldn’t deter me if they pop up, lol. 😂🚑

@MSCasting @WBEngMG and Maria M - thank you SO much for entering the thread and giving us the link. you are the best! if you have any tips for WA State, my time in the appt roulette is approaching... :)
@WBEngMG @MSCasting yes!! congrats. will be interested to hear if any of the protesters are still lurking about the stadium entry.
@WBEngMG @laRosalind Yay! That’s so wonderful!!! 🥰🙌
@laRosalind @MSCasting I’m scheduled for a Moderna vaccine this coming Wednesday! Dodger Stadium here I come, lol. Thank you so much to the both you 💕
@WBEngMG @MSCasting fabulous!  and re. J&J - they are having manufacturing issues and my state (WA) and CA have both announced that they don't expect any new supply for about 3 weeks.

@WBEngMG @laRosalind Wonderful! J & J MIGHT be harder to get than Moderna at Dodgers Stadium, but I hope I’m wrong! I’m sending positive vibes that you get an appointment quickly and that doing so alleviates some stress. All the best!!
@MSCasting @laRosalind Yep! I used your search app and was able to see appointments- I’m registering with the provider now and looking for a J-J appointment at Dodger Stadium - thank you both!
@WBEngMG @laRosalind I just did a quick search and found one for Tuesday.
@WBEngMG @laRosalind Did you search via carbon health? I can help you, if you’d like. Just DM me and I can contact you directly when I see an open spot.

@laRosalind @MSCasting Thank you! I just tried and got zero appts available returned... but, it didn’t return Dodger Stadium as a choice and it’s closer than USC so something is wrong with the link I got emailed from the CA Dept of Health. I’m going online to figure this out, thx!
@MSCasting @WBEngMG Thanks Maria M. for the tip! And Maria G - i just experimented and found open appts this week at Dodger Stadium & a few other sites. Good luck!!
@WBEngMG @laRosalind Dodgers Stadium has had lots of openings since Thursday, have you been using this website to check? https://t.co/dAHvf9rpNo
@laRosalind I heard about this... I’m close to Dodger Stadium - I will try this as a ‘last resort’, thx

@WBEngMG wouldn't schedule 2nd shot, so she went thru the same hell once again. finally she just drove to Dodger Stadium end of day and got in line. when they saw proof of first vacc they gave her the 2nd. a ridiculous, fucked up system.

@WBEngMG i'm so sorry. good friend in L.A. was going through same hell. finally a "friend of a friend who knew somebody" at the Dodger Stadium site called w/the end of day 'get down here now' extra doses available.

@laRosalind I’m so fk’g fed up w/ checking the damn web site 4-6 times a day trying to get an appt (and trying every damn site - which can only be done by inputting each one individually (15+ sites! - and doing this for each type of vaccine (I’ll take anything now))). I’m ready to give up...

Meaning we are all now going to be playing our own version of "Hunger Games" as we all fight each other over the very limited vaccination slots. But you do you - you've already been fully vaccinated and have moved on to the next hot story... /fin

While our Governors garner positive press by issuing feel-good decrees stating ALL shall now be eligible for vaccination, this doesn't change the fact there is not yet enough supply to vaccinate those already eligible. /2
